name: BMO Canadian Dividend ETF
longDescription: The ETF seeks to provide a balance of income and potential for long-term capital appreciation, primarily by investing in ETFs that provide exposure to a diversified portfolio of global equity and fixed income securities. To achieve investment objective the investment strategy of the ETF is to invest in and hold the constituent securities of the Index in the same proportion as they are held in the Index. The Manager may also use a sampling methodology in selecting investments for the ETF to obtain exposure to the performance of the Index. As an alternative to or in conjunction with investing in and holding all or some of the constituent securities of the Index, the ETF may invest in or use Other Securities as defined in the prospectus to obtain exposure to the performance of the Index.
